Tags:
  - Combat-Action=Metanoia=‘Duo Sunt in Homine’
  - 329
By: Hermes
---
Man has two souls. One of them comes from the first Intelligible, and
partakes of the power of the Demiurgus： the other soul is put into
the man by the revolution of the heavenly bodies, and into this latter
soul enters subsequently the (first) soul which is able to see God.
